---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TravelingWaveAnimation from "~/components/research/TravelingWaveAnimation.astro";
import katex from "katex";

const m = (tex: string) => katex.renderToString(tex, { throwOnError: false });
const md = (tex: string) =>
  katex.renderToString(tex, { throwOnError: false, displayMode: true });
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Animation · Traveling-Wave"
  description="Interactive animation of the traveling-wave Stirling thermoacoustic engine (TASHE): loop topology, isothermal Stirling cycle in the regenerator, p–u in phase, energy flow (work flow / heat flow); toggle between a mechanical α-Stirling engine and the acoustic loop."
>
  <section class="py-8">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-brand-500">Research / Animations</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-900">
      Thermoacoustic Mechanism Animation
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-xl font-light tracking-wide text-brand-600">Traveling-Wave Type · 行波型</p>
    <div class="mt-3 h-1 w-16 bg-accent-500" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
      The <a href="/en/research/animations/standing-wave" class="underline hover:text-accent-600"
        >standing-wave type</a
      > relies on the <strong>irreversible</strong> <span set:html={m("W_{stand}")} /> and its
      efficiency is limited. The traveling-wave type places the gas parcel in a
      <strong>circulating loop</strong> and uses a <strong>regenerator</strong> to keep the parcel in
      <strong>isothermal</strong> contact with the walls, realizing a <strong
        >reversible Stirling cycle</strong
      > driven by <span set:html={m("W_{prog}")} /> — with efficiency <strong
        >approaching Carnot</strong
      >. Below we cover only what differs from the standing-wave type (parcel oscillation, <span
        set:html={m("p'\\!-\\!\\xi'")}
      /> = work flow density, the traveling/standing decomposition, etc. are explained on the
      standing-wave page).
    </p>
  </section>

  <TravelingWaveAnimation lang="en" />

  <section class="mt-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-900">Three keys of the traveling-wave type</h2>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-brand-800">① Loop + regenerator: why reversible</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">
      A pure traveling wave needs a <strong>loop</strong> to sustain itself (a straight tube only
      supports standing waves). The <strong>regenerator</strong> on the loop is a dense mesh whose
      <strong>pore radius is far smaller than the thermal diffusion length</strong> (<span
        set:html={m("r \\ll \\delta_\\alpha")}
      />, <span set:html={m("r")} />: channel radius, <span set:html={m("\\delta_\\alpha")} />:
      thermal diffusion length, subscript <span set:html={m("\\alpha")} /> = thermal diffusivity).
      Fine enough pores → the parcel stays <strong>isothermal</strong> with the wall → the heat
      exchange is <strong>reversible</strong>. Contrast the standing-wave stack (plate spacing <span
        set:html={m("\\sim \\delta_\\alpha")}
      />, imperfect contact → irreversible).
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-brand-800">
      ② <span set:html={m("p")} />–<span set:html={m("u")} /> in phase → Stirling cycle
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">
      In a traveling wave the pressure <span set:html={m("p'")} /> and velocity <span
        set:html={m("u'")}
      /> are <strong>in phase</strong> (a standing wave has them <span set:html={m("90^\\circ")} />
      apart). The parcel therefore <strong
        >moves toward the hot end while compressed and toward the cold end while expanded</strong
      >, completing an isothermal-compression → isothermal-expansion Stirling cycle in the
      regenerator — the <span set:html={m("p")} />–<span set:html={m("V")} /> trace is a
      <strong>fat loop</strong> (area = work, reversible). The standing-wave type draws a thin one.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-brand-800">
      ③ Energy flow: heat flow <span set:html={m("\\bar Q")} /> becomes work flow <span
        set:html={m("\\bar I")}
      />
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">
      Seen as <strong>energy flows</strong>: heat flow <span set:html={m("\\bar Q")} /> enters at
      the hot exchanger and is converted along the regenerator into <strong
        >work flow <span set:html={m("\\bar I")} /></strong
      > — the acoustic power <span set:html={m("\\bar I")} /> is <strong>amplified along the way</strong
      >. The two satisfy
    </p>
    <div set:html={md("\\frac{d(\\bar I+\\bar Q)}{dx}=0,\\qquad W_{prog}=\\beta\\,\\frac{dT_m}{dx}\\,\\chi'_a\\,I")}></div>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
      <span set:html={m("W_{prog}")} />: work source of the traveling-wave component (acoustic power
      produced per unit length), proportional to <span set:html={m("\\chi'_a")} /> (the real part of
      the thermal-response function — <strong>reversible</strong> heat exchange) → it <strong
        >amplifies <span set:html={m("I")} /></strong
      > rather than dissipating. <span set:html={m("\\beta")} />: thermal expansion coefficient,
      <span set:html={m("T_m")} />: mean temperature, <span set:html={m("dT_m/dx")} />: regenerator
      temperature gradient. (See the <a
        href="/en/research/animations/standing-wave"
        class="underline hover:text-accent-600">standing-wave page</a
      > for the definitions of <span set:html={m("\\bar I,\\bar Q,\\chi'_a")} />.)
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-900">Standing vs traveling</h2>
    <table class="mt-4 w-full text-sm">
      <thead class="text-left text-brand-700">
        <tr class="border-b-2 border-brand-200">
          <th class="py-2 pr-4"></th>
          <th class="py-2 pr-4">Standing-wave type</th>
          <th class="py-2">Traveling-wave type</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-gray-700">
        <tr class="border-b border-brand-100">
          <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Geometry</td>
          <td class="py-2 pr-4">straight resonator</td>
          <td class="py-2">loop</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-brand-100">
          <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Core component</td>
          <td class="py-2 pr-4">stack (spacing <span set:html={m("\\sim\\delta_\\alpha")} />)</td>
          <td class="py-2">regenerator (pores <span set:html={m("\\ll\\delta_\\alpha")} />)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-brand-100">
          <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium"
            ><span set:html={m("p")} />–<span set:html={m("u")} /> phase</td
          >
          <td class="py-2 pr-4"><span set:html={m("90^\\circ")} /></td>
          <td class="py-2">in phase</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-brand-100">
          <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Parcel cycle</td>
          <td class="py-2 pr-4">thin loop</td>
          <td class="py-2">fat Stirling loop</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-brand-100">
          <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Energy conversion</td>
          <td class="py-2 pr-4"
            ><span set:html={m("W_{stand}\\propto\\chi''_a")} /> (irreversible)</td
          >
          <td class="py-2"><span set:html={m("W_{prog}\\propto\\chi'_a")} /> (reversible)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Efficiency</td>
          <td class="py-2 pr-4">lower</td>
          <td class="py-2">near Carnot</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-x-5 gap-y-2 text-sm text-gray-500">
      <a href="/en/research/animations" class="underline hover:text-accent-600"
        >← Back to animations</a
      >
      <a href="/en/research/animations/standing-wave" class="underline hover:text-accent-600"
        >Standing-wave type</a
      >
      <a href="/en/research/thermoacoustic-effect" class="underline hover:text-accent-600"
        >The thermoacoustic effect</a
      >
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
